s%2C%20I%20wouldn't%20have%20had%20the%20time%20for%20personal%20growth.%20I%20had%20to%20prioritize%20my%20job%20and%20personal%20learning%20while%20also%20taking%20care%20of%20a%20new%20daughter.%20My%20wife%20also%20had%20to%20sacrifice%20a%20lot%20of%20hours%20for%20me%20to%20work%20on%20my%20own%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f48b5d29-7ea7-4f42-b581-28f4bbd28c2d%5C%22%3ESolo%20projects%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20books%20don't%20typically%20come%20with%20assignments%2C%20but%20the%20courses%20come%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20hands-on%20exercises.%20Over%20time%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20was%20the%20missing%20piece%20in%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%20It%20was%20getting%20difficult%20to%20convince%20hiring%20managers%20that%20I%20could%20do%20the%20job%20because%20it%20required%20building%20demos%20and%20doing%20hands-on%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20I%20had%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-vp-shares-how-entry-level-engineers-can-stand-out-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edo%20my%20own%20projects%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20AI%20tools%20were%20incredibly%20helpful%20for%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20other%20people%20who%20want%20to%20transition%2C%20I%20would%20say%20you%20need%20to%20keep%20working%20hard.%20It%20takes%20time%20for%20you%20to%20connect%20the%20dots%20on%20complex%20problems%20and%20sometimes%20you%20have%20to%20read%20the%20same%20thing%20again%20and%20again%20to%20nail%20that%20concept%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20people%20who%20want%20to%20get%20into%20AI%2C%20including%20me%2C%20are%20in%20a%20rush%20to%20land%20an%20AI%20job%20after%20six%20months.%20But%20a%20lot%20of%20concepts%20in%20machine%20learning%20take%20time%20to%20internalize.%20So%20persistence%20is%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20work%20in%20an%20AI%20role%3F%20We%20want%20to%20hear%20from%20you.%20Contact%20the%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C